Package com.CMPUT301W24T32.brazmascheckin.models

Class Event

java.lang.Object
com.CMPUT301W24T32.brazmascheckin.models.Event
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable
public class Event extends Object implements Serializable
The Event class represents an event entity with various attributes such as ID, name, date, description, etc. It includes methods for handling check-ins, sign-ups, and other event-related operations.

      Constructs a new instance of the Event class with the full information for an event.
      Parameters:
      ID - Identification assigned by FirestoreDB
      name - Name of the event
      date - Date of the event
      description - Description of the event
      checkIns - Attendees who have checked in, including number of times they have checked in
      signUps - Attendees who have signed up
      attendeeLimit - Maximum number of attendees who can check-in
      posterID - Reference to the image
      QRCodeID - Reference to the image
      shareQRCodeID - Reference to the image
      organizer - Reference to the user who created the event
      geoLocationEnabled - If geolocation is enabled
      eventLocation - the location of the event
      userLocationPairs - the list of users who have checked in, and where they have checked in
